Idiffer.

Hideramblings


The escape craft isn't huge. I think it's reasonable that its interior is visible through a foot-wide opening. That being said, I forgot to make the hatch wide enough for -1 to fit through it, so I changed it to .73m wide.

The purpose for the hatch's composition is ambiguous. I don't think it's made of glass so that the Foundation can see through it, but perhaps so that something can see through it. It also hints that the craft wasn't designed with -1 in mind, but the Foundation doesn't have enough information to conclude this. The backstory is intentionally vague.

There's not much dust in the moon's vicinity at all. Some scientists hypothesize that lunar regolith particles may rise meters or kilometers above the surface via electrostatic levitation before falling back down, but it has never been confirmed. Even if the  hypothesis is correct, I doubt much damage would have been caused until the vessel neared the surface. And it was falling to the surface pretty quick before it exploded. And for what it's worth there is a tail of sodium atoms in the Moon's wake, but it's pretty dang thin. Anyway, it is generally held that the Moon is surrounded by a vacuum. Its atmosphere is negligible.



05:13 Extraterrestrial vessel appears in flash of white light at an altitude of approximately 130,000m above far side of moon.
